The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [ISO/IEC 18670 SoftWare Hash IDentifier (SWHID) Specification V1.2](https://www.iso.org/standard/89985.html) and they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Gitoid](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/prov/gitoid), stands for [Git Object ID](https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Internals-Git-Objects). A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [ISO/IEC 18670 SoftWare Hash IDentifier (SWHID) Specification V1.2](https://www.iso.org/standard/89985.html) and they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

Necessary actions include requesting assistance or information about the vulnerability, as well as publishing a notification either internally and/or externally. Typically, internal groups would meet to determine the overall response and then execute agreed upon actions. CISA recommends remediating Act vulnerabilities as soon as possible.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vcs

For AI training dataset, test dataset, test artifact, configuration data, build input data, and build output data, please consider using the more specific relationship types: `trainedOn`, `testedOn`, `hasTest`, `configures`, `hasInputs`, and `hasOutputs`, respectively. This relationship does not imply dependency.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: underInvestigationFor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) The `from` Vulnerability impact is being investigated for each `to` Element. The use of the `underInvestigationFor` type is constrained to `VexUnderInvestigationVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.
Provides a License author's preferred text to indicate that a file is covered by the License.
An Individual Value for License when no assertion can be made about its actual value.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: any hashing algorithm that does not exist in this list of entries
Records the biases that the dataset is known to encompass.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: kilowattHour
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Kilowatt-hour.
Captures the domain in which the AI package can be used.
Specifies until when the artifact can be used before its usage needs to be reassessed.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: coordinatedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) The `from` Vulnerability is coordinatedBy the `to` Agent(s) (vendor, researcher, or consumer agent).
Specifies the CVSS vector string for a vulnerability.
Indicates the amount of energy consumption incurred by an AI model.
Specifies whether an additional text identifier has been marked as deprecated.
Describes one a profile which the creator of this ElementCollection intends to conform to.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The third-highest level of risk posed by an AI system.
Information about the relationship between two Elements.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasPrerequisite
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element has a prerequisite on each `to` Element, during a LifecycleScopeType period.
Specifies the safety risk level.
Identify the version of a package.
References the Element on the left-hand side of a relationship.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: source
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a single or a collection of source files
Provides the location of an external reference.
Provides a set of values to be used to describe the common types of SBOMs that tools may create.
Describes what the given dataset should be used for.
Specifies the CVSS qualitative severity rating of a vulnerability in relation to a piece of software.
An Element an annotator has made an assertion about.
Describes a mechanism to update the dataset.
Provides the license under which the SPDX documentation of the Element can be used.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandsTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` archive expands out as an artifact described by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: install
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is used to install software on disk
A mathematical algorithm that maps data of arbitrary size to a bit string.
Records a hyperparameter used to build the AI model contained in the AI package.
Specifies the unit of energy consumption.
Describes a sensor used for collecting the data.
Property describing the session in which a build is invoked.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: secureSoftwareAttestation
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to information assuring that the software is developed using security practices as defined by [NIST SP 800-218 Secure Software Development Framework (SSDF) Version 1.1](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/218/final) or [CISA Secure Software Development Attestation Form](https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/secure-software-development-attestation-form).
Represents the energy quantity.
Provides an indication of where to retrieve an external Element.
Specifies the amount of energy consumed during inference time by an AI model that is being used in the AI system.
Provides a place for the SPDX data creator to record the package URL string (in accordance with the Package URL specification) for a software Package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: file
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The file represents a single file (default).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cve
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures identifiers, an identifier for a specific software flaw defined within the official CVE Dictionary and that conforms to the [CVE specification](https://csrc.nist.gov/glossary/term/cve_id).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: trackStar
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: ("Track*" in the SSVC spec) The vulnerability contains specific characteristics that may require closer monitoring for changes. CISA recommends remediating Track* vulnerabilities within standard update timelines.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: socialMedia
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a social media channel for a package.
Categories of presence or absence.
Contains a URL where the License or LicenseAddition can be found in use.
Specifies the CVSS base, temporal, threat, or environmental severity type.
Indicates the type of support that is associated with an artifact.
Provide consumers with comments by the creator of the Element about the Element.
Specifies the exploit catalog type.
Specifies whether the License is listed as free by the [Free Software Foundation (FSF)](https://fsf.org).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: republishedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability's details were tracked, aggregated, and/or enriched to improve context (i.e. NVD) by each `to` Agent.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAssociatedVulnerability
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Used to associate a `from` Artifact with each `to` Vulnerability.
Provides information about the completeness of relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha3_256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-3 with a digest length of 256, as defined in [FIPS 202](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/fips/202/final).
Capture the scope of information about a specific relationship between elements.
Provides information about the content type of an Element or a Property.
Specifies the type of the external reference.
Specifies the type of an external reference.
Specifies an Extension characterization of some aspect of an Element.
Defines the line range in the original host file that the snippet information applies to.
A place for the SPDX document creator to record a website that serves as the package's home page.
Captures a limitation of the AI software.
